LustreError: 2787:0:(osd_object.c:913:osd_attr_set()) FS-OST0000: failed to update accounting ZAP for user 111 (-2)&lt;br/&gt;
LustreError: 2586:0:(osd_object.c:577:osd_object_destroy()) FS-OST0000: failed to remove &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x100000000:0x784a3:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; from accounting ZAP for usr 111: rc = -2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="123561" author="lexsoft" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2015 02:03:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;During active use &quot;mixed I/O workload&quot;, delete or upload the files, an error occurs, after which the system restarts unexpectedly.&lt;br/&gt;
Quotas are set through commands&lt;br/&gt;
lctl conf_param FS.quota.mdt=ug&lt;br/&gt;
lctl conf_param FS.quota.ost=ug&lt;br/&gt;
Though the command &apos;lctl conf_param&apos; is deprecated, but works as opposed to the &apos;lctl set_param -P&apos;.&lt;br/&gt;
The command &apos;lctl set_param -P FS.quota.mdt=ug&apos; does not work, then there is no set quota&lt;br/&gt;
You may need to add about this issue in another query&lt;br/&gt;
I believe the solution to this problem at the moment, if you do not use the quota for a user simply turn off? Having read the threads you specify on the links&lt;br/&gt;
What data do you need to provide more?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="123495" author="adilger" created="Thu, 6 Aug 2015 18:04:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Having some more information about what triggered this problem, and what kind of configuration you are using is needed before we could even start looking at this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that the patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/15294&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/15294&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2435&quot; title=&quot;inode accounting in osd-zfs is racy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2435&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2435&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; osd-zfs: use zfs native dnode accounting&quot; that will replace this quota code completely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
